Title: HMS Barfleur (1768)
Text:  HMS Barfleur was a 90-gun second-rate ship of the line of the Royal Navy designed by Sir Thomas Slade on the lines of the 100-gun ship Royal William and launched at Chatham Dockyard on 30 July 1768 at a cost of £49222. In about 1780 she had another eight guns added to her quarterdeck making her a 98-gun ship; she possessed a crew of approximately 750. Her design class sisters were the Prince George Princess Royal and Formidable.
